## 13) What `vm-control` would actually run

For start:

```bash
systemctl start pgvm-postgres.service
```

For stop with defaults:

```bash
rm -f /run/pgvm/stop.env
systemctl stop pgvm-postgres.service
```

For stop with smart mode:

```bash
cat > /run/pgvm/stop.env <<'EOF'
PG_STOP_MODE=smart
PG_STOP_TIMEOUT=300
EOF
systemctl stop pgvm-postgres.service
```

For basebackup:

```bash
cat > /run/pgvm/op.env <<'EOF'
PG_BB_PGMAJOR=16
PG_BB_BIN_DIR=/usr/pgsql-16/bin
PG_BB_SOURCE_CONNSTR=host=10.0.0.10 port=5432 user=replicator dbname=postgres
PG_BB_TARGET_DIR=/data/local/mydb/16/data
PG_BB_WAL_METHOD=stream
PG_BB_PROGRESS=yes
PG_BB_WRITE_RECOVERY_CONF=yes
EOF
systemctl start pgvm-postgres-op@basebackup.service
```

